radiographic_examinations.findings: A few nonspecific foci of hyperintensity in the frontal subcortical white matter, seen on T2-weighted and fluid-attenuated inversion recovery (FLAIR) images.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: MRI of the cervical, thoracic, and lumbar spine
radiographic_examinations.findings: Degenerative changes of the cervical and lumbar spine, without cord or nerve-root compression.
A mildly enhancing left axillary lymph node, 9 mm in greatest dimension. No other suspicious lymph nodes are identified.

Ill-defined hyperintensity on FLAIR images in the amygdala, hippocampus, and parahippocampal gyri bilaterally, more prominent in the left temporal lobe than in the right temporal lobe, with mild local mass effect.
